Object:
-------

Java is Class based object oreinted programming language.

why object?
Re usablity

If there is a class there will be an object
If no class , no object
For a class we can create any number of objects

public class FirstProgram{
	

}

new keyword:
-----------

If we want to create an object we have to use new keyword.


class FirstProgram{
	

}

int a=10;


FirstProgram fp =  new FirstProgram();

A copy of class will be created inside Heap Area.

Demo

Demo d = new Demo();

Sample

Sample s= new Sample();


String

String str= new String();


Dot opeartor:
--------------

.

objectName.prpertyname;


package com.demo.object;

public class Customer {

	String customerName= "raj";
}


package com.demo.object;

public class App {

	public static void main(String[] args) {

		Customer cust = new Customer();
		System.out.println(cust.customerName);

	}
}
 	


package com.demo.object;

public class App {

	public static void main(String[] args) {

		Customer cust = new Customer();
		System.out.println(cust.customerName);
		
		Customer cust1 = new Customer();
		System.out.println(cust1.customerName);

	}
}















